$ v$sql_cursor

`v$sql_cursor` records information about each cursor that is currently active(?) in the current session (i.e. the session that is querying `v$sql_cursor`).

{ Join with v$sqlarea

   Join `parent_handle` with address of → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/sql[`v$sql`]
   or → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/sql/area[`v$sqlarea`].

  gh|oracle-patterns|/Installed/dynamic-performance-views/sql/cursor/join-sqlarea.sql||

}

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/open_cursor[`v$open_cursor`]
 
  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views[Oracle Dynamic Performance Views]
